§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A polynomial $p: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ is ❬nonnegative❭ (a ❬nonnegative
    polynomial❭, ❬nonnegative real polynomial❭) if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p(x) ≥ 0 \quad \text{for all } x ∈ 𝗥 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ In this case, we call $p$ ❬positive semidefinite❭ or ❬PSD❭. ⦉
⦉

§ Testing nonnegativity ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Given polynomial $p$, how do we know if $p$ is (globally)
    nonnegative? ⦉

  ‖ Consider $p: 𝗥 → 𝗥$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p(x) = 5x^4 - 4x^3 - x^2 + 2x + 2 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

